  "In many countries, McDonald's adapts its menu to local tastes: serving McAloo Tikki in India, Teriyaki burgers in Japan, and McArabia in the Middle East. What cultural process does this adaptation represent?": "",
  "Cultural divergence caused by McDonald's according to widely held views on this topic": "",
  "Glocalization: a global company adapting its products to local cultural preferences, representing a blend of globalization and localization": "",
  "Complete cultural assimilation by McDonald's according to widely held views on this topic": "",
  "The failure of globalization in these countries, especially during periods of significant change": "",
  "This exemplifies glocalization: the adaptation of global products and practices to local contexts. McDonald's maintains its global brand while adapting to local food taboos, tastes, and cultural preferences, demonstrating how globalization and local culture interact.": "",
  "Korean pop music (K-pop), Korean dramas, and Korean beauty products have become globally popular, a phenomenon known as the 'Korean Wave' (Hallyu). This cultural export was supported by government policy. What type of diffusion does the Korean Wave primarily represent?": "",
  "Only stimulus diffusion when the interaction between Korean and diffusion factors is taken into full account": "",
  "Reverse hierarchical diffusion from small towns to cities in most scenarios involving Korean factors": "",
